
# 🔍 PolicyLens: AI-Powered Insurance Advocacy
> **Turning 50-page legal "traps" into clear, actionable health security.**

[![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.10+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/)
[![Streamlit](https://img.shields.io/badge/Frontend-Streamlit-FF4B4B.svg)](https://streamlit.io/)
[![Groq](https://img.shields.io/badge/LLM-Groq%20Llama%203-orange.svg)](https://groq.com/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

## 📌 The Problem
Most Indian insurance policies are written in "Legalese"—complex jargon designed to protect the insurer, not the insured. Policyholders often discover "Clause 12, Subsection 4" only *after* a claim is rejected during a medical crisis. 

**PolicyLens** solves this by using specialized LLM agents to act as a **Senior Indian Insurance Lawyer** in your pocket.

---

## 🛠️ The 3-Phase Solution

### 🛡️ Phase 1: Intelligent Policy Audit
* **Automated Extraction:** High-speed parsing of multi-page PDFs using `PyMuPDF`.
* **The 4-Quadrant View:** Instant categorization into **Covered**, **Not Covered**, **Conditional**, and **Waiting Periods**.
* **Health Scoring:** An algorithmic rating (0-100) based on IRDAI benchmarks, flagging high-risk exclusions.

### 📅 Phase 2: Claim Scenario Simulator
* **Predictive Eligibility:** "Will my father's heart attack be covered if he had surgery 2 years ago?"
* **Visual Roadmap:** Generates a dynamic timeline showing exactly when specific waiting periods end.

### ⚖️ Phase 3: Legal Fightback Engine
* **Escalation Guidance:** A 5-step roadmap from internal GRO appeals to the Insurance Ombudsman.
* **Auto-Drafting:** Generates legally-sound, professional appeal emails tailored to your specific rejection letter and policy clauses.
* **Ombudsman Directory:** Built-in database of contact details for major Indian metros.

---

## 🏗️ Technical Architecture & Optimizations
The core challenge of this project was balancing **LLM precision** with **API rate limits (TPM/RPD)** on the Groq Free Tier.

* **Dual-Model Pipeline:** * `Llama-3.3-70b-versatile` for high-reasoning tasks (Health Scoring & Clause Analysis).
    * `Llama-3.1-8b-instant` for high-speed tasks (Scenario Simulation & Email Drafting).
* **Rate-Limit Management:** Implemented context-window slicing (6,000 char limit) and `time.sleep` intervals to stay within 12,000 TPM limits.
* **Persona Engineering:** System prompts hardcoded with 20+ years of "Indian Insurance Law" context to reduce hallucinations.

---

## 🚀 Quick Start

### 1. Prerequisites
* Python 3.10+
* A Groq API Key ([Get it here](https://console.groq.com/))
* An ngrok token (if running via Google Colab)

### 2. Installation
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/PolicyLens.git
cd PolicyLens
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Execution (Local)
```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

